    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - CAB TILTING - CAB TILT HYDRAULIC
        SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM</title>
        <para>The cab tilt hydraulic system (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601890">Figure 90</hotlnk>) uses two hydraulic lift cylinders (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601890">Item 34, Figure 90</hotlnk>) which are actuated by the hydraulic lift pump which
            can be either manual (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601890">Item 16, Figure 90</hotlnk>) or air powered (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1601890">Item 20, Figure 90</hotlnk>). (This pump also provides the hydraulic pressure for
            the automatic release of cab latch hook.)
        </para>
